<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="415" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d415">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1031</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-26T17:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1273. Referring to third paragraph Department’s 1208, December 10, 3
                                    p.m.,<note n="2" xml:id="d415fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_466">p.
                                    466</ref>.</note> you may furnish your British and French
                                colleagues with information contained in your 2261, <persName corresp="#p_AFE1">Anderson</persName>’s cable No. 9.<note n="3" xml:id="d415fn3">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_478">p.
                                    478</ref>.</note> Paraphrases thereof have been furnished
                                British and French Ambassadors here to-day.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>